#week-title("Four", "Saturn, Lead & The Binah–Tiphereth Arc")

=== Core Teaching

The alchemical arc from Lead to Gold is, on the Tree of Life, the arc from
Binah (Saturn, the Great Limiter, the first fixed form) to Tiphereth (Sun,
the heart of the Work, the gold principle). This is not merely a symbolic
correspondence — it is the map of what the metallic work is philosophically
trying to accomplish.

*Binah (Saturn/Lead).* The third sephirah: Understanding, the Great Mother,
the first limitation that gives form to the undifferentiated force of Chokmah.
Binah is the principle that says "this and not that" — the contracting,
crystallising force without which form is impossible. Lead embodies this
principle in the mineral kingdom: heavy, contracting, patient to the point
of immobility. Binah is also the sphere of Time — Saturn's association with
time, with the slow crystallisation of geological ages, with the patience
required of the alchemist.

*Tiphereth (Sun/Gold).* The sixth sephirah: Beauty, the Heart, the balance
of the Tree. Tiphereth is the central point from which all other spheres are
visible and by which all are balanced. It is the sphere of redemption in the
Qabalistic tradition — the point where the descending lightning flash from
Kether reaches its reflective midpoint before returning upward. Gold embodies
this principle: incorruptible, balanced, radiating warmth equally in all
directions.

*The path between them.* The paths connecting Binah to Tiphereth on the Tree
pass through the Abyss (the great discontinuity between the Supernal Triad
and the lower seven sephiroth) and through Chesed (Jupiter/Tin) — the sphere
of mercy, expansion, and abundance. The journey from lead to gold therefore
passes through Jupiter: through the expansion and multiplication that follows
the initial limitation. Tin is not a goal in itself — it is a waypoint on the
arc from the Saturnine beginning to the Solar completion.

*The NDT Double-Digit Delineations* for numbers 13–22 map the Major Arcana's
advanced stages onto this arc. The Death card (13) at the Scorpio path marks
the dissolution of the Saturnine lead structure; the Star (17) at Aquarius
marks the Albedo; the Sun (19) at its own sphere marks the Citrinitas; and
Judgement (20) marks the Rubedo — the resurrection and projection of the Stone.

=== Topics This Week

- Binah as Saturn/Lead on the Tree: the principle of limitation and crystallisation
- Tiphereth as Sun/Gold: the heart, beauty, and the goal of the metallic work
- The path between: through Chesed/Jupiter/Tin as intermediate stage
- The Major Arcana Death through Judgement mapped onto the lead-to-gold arc

#inner-work[
  *The Full Arc Contemplated*

  Lay out the Major Arcana cards Death (13), Temperance (14), The Tower (16),
  The Star (17), The Moon (18), The Sun (19), and Judgement (20) in sequence.

  Contemplate these seven cards as a narrative of the metallic arc from the
  dissolution of lead to the projection of gold. Spend three to five minutes
  with each card. Record what each reveals about the stage of the Work it
  represents — not as abstract symbol but as something you have experienced,
  in some form, across the three years of study.
]

